  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nairobi informal settlement sanitation project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poor sanitation is a major problem in all slum or informal settlements in Nairobi.  An absence of sewer lines and lack of available land for on -plot sanitation are major obstacles to increasing sanitation coverage.   This project aims to work with existing stakeholders and pilot two technologies (urine diversion latrines &amp; improved bucket latrine) which we believe have potential for replication and scale up within informal settlements.</narrative>
  </description>
